{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_01WR8n55VR9ZeHdubSTsimzr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All goals are met:\n\n- **app-producer** is `1/1 Running` (Ready), no restarts since the fix.\n- **`/app` vhost** contains **`app-queue`** of type **`classic`**, and messages are accumulating (10 and growing).\n- **Cluster** remains healthy with all **3 nodes** (`rabbitmq-0/1/2`) running as disk nodes.\n\n**Root cause:** the setup job granted `app-user` write/read permissions on `/app` but left `configure` permission empty (`\"\"`), so the management API rejected the `PUT /queues/%2Fapp/app-queue` declare call with `not_authorised`, crash-looping the producer. Fixed by running `rabbitmqctl set_permissions -p /app app-user \".*\" \".*\" \".*\"` to grant configure rights — no data loss, no CRDs/operators involved. (Note: the job's `force-quorum` policy also silently failed — `queue-type` isn't a valid RabbitMQ policy key — so it never actually threatened the classic queue type; no action was needed there.)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":438,"cache_read_input_tokens":56647,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":438},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b8300cb7-fe62-4714-8b1e-d3bb3ee4e955","uuid":"4098465e-0424-423c-b707-b8bfe749c210","request_id":"req_011CcajBF2N3cNdRZHeAejqF"}
